<item>
            <title>[HBASE-1999] When HTable goes away, close zk session in shutdown hook or something...</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1999</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, while there is a close on HTable, it does not let go of the zk session.. it does not call close... because the session is shared by all HTables in the VM.  Add a shutdown hook that will close zk on the way out.   Otherwise it makes for session timeouts in zk server logs.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12441355">HBASE-1999</key>
            <summary>When HTable goes away, close zk session in shutdown hook or something...</summary>
